text: I am haunted by the story of my love for Edina (edamame), which is also the story of my first, perhaps my only, love: the absurdity of life.
My iPhone can't do mass texts, so happy new year! I love you all! Add me to your mass texts yo!
Trying to hijack a cable car
Okay, I am finally learning how to tie a bowtie after keeping this one tied since purchased.
Getting a mani pedi.
Just left Reno to enter California, land of my birthing, for two nights only!
161 to Reno! Question book interviewing commencing! The "uncomfortable moments"  could've tried a bit harder.
Holy Joseph Smith please get us off of the blizzardy Utah mountain safely!
We're entering a snow storm!
A beautiful cold and sunny day, perfect to cross the Rockies! I see them on the horizon now...
Kellianne lived in Boulder in 1996 and has wanted to come back to this diner, Village Coffee, for "56 billion years"! It is awesome!
How are we supposed to hit the road when High Fidelity is on tv?
We made it to Columbus, Missouri today... 600 miles. Mediocre Greek food in St Louis.
90% chance of snow tomorrow! Shitballs.
Smoking is allowed in St Louis kebab houses apparently! So hungry... and not for Sweeney Todd meat pies.
Red bull? Check!
Listening to Illinoise as we enter Illinois... how many fellow drivers are doing the same?
Kellianne wouldn't pull the wings off a beautiful butterfly in exchange for a vacation anywhere in the world. I would.
We got Sweeney Todd... but are saving it for nighttime.
51 miles to Columbus, OH... where we will procure audiobooks. Any suggestions?
423 miles in our first sorta half day. Resting at at America's Best Value somewhere in Ohio. Smells like "clean".
We're in Pennslyvania now... 70 miles til the next rest stop. The junk food has arrived.
2,818 miles to San Fransisco. From one end of I-70 to the other!
Activated my new iPhone, and got on I-70 headed west!
Budget Rental is bullshit, they wouldn't give us a car without a major credit card... now we're chicken-bussing it to Delaware tonight a ...
omorrow!
Not much sleep on the plane last night... I hate being sleepy!
Last 4 flights on JetBlue: 3 hrs late, 6 hrs late, canceled, and 2 hrs late with bad info online. Lame dude!
Just launched our new simpler 43 Things homepage for logged out peeps.
I barely made my plane which was 6 hours late! 4am is inhuman!
The wisest words ever spoken, "you had to be there."
